            <bug_when>2014-03-13 14:31:35 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>The selection manager will be set by qx.ui.virtual.selection.MModel to the virtual widgets (tree, list). This mixin creates an instance of the qx.ui.virtual.selection.Row on qx.ui.virtual.selection.MModel#_initSelectionManager

I would recommended make it configurable to define the selected manager.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>41145</commentid>
            <who name="Mustafa Sak">mustafa.sak</who>
            <bug_when>2014-09-08 13:00:11 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>After a second glance it does not make sense to add an API to make the selection manager configurable. First qx.ui.virtual.selection.MModel is heavily reliant on qx.ui.virtual.selection.Row.

So it is a good idea to override qx.ui.virtual.selection.MModel#_initSelectionManager to change selection manager and the delegation.</thetext>
